1
00:00:00,031 --> 00:00:19,271
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Harato Sambha Sambhudassa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Harato Sambha Sambhudassa

2
00:00:19,251 --> 00:00:33,654
Namo tassa bhagavato harato samma sambuddhassa Homage to the Buddha, the blessed, noble and fully self-enlightened one.

3
00:00:37,219 --> 00:00:40,264
So we're now moving on to the next...

4
00:00:43,112 --> 00:01:11,584
piece of scripture where we're in the section on the tribulations of an unreflected living on unreflected living so if you remember last week we talked about you know these two darts how we make suffering for ourselves by our reactions to things so this particular part of the scripture is really talking about the vicissitudes of life the eight worldly conditions

5
00:01:12,441 --> 00:01:16,128
I shall read it and then we'll see what we can make of it.

6
00:01:16,147 --> 00:01:25,364
These eight worldly conditions keep the world turning round and the world turns round these eight worldly conditions.

7
00:01:26,305 --> 00:01:26,846
What eight?

8
00:01:27,789 --> 00:01:33,858
Gain and loss, fame and disrepute, praise and blame, pleasure and pain.

9
00:01:35,171 --> 00:01:43,780
These eight worldly conditions are encountered by an uninstructed worldling and they are also encountered by an instructed noble disciple.

10
00:01:44,820 --> 00:01:53,289
What now is the distinction, the disparity, the difference between an instructed noble disciple and an uninstructed worldling?

11
00:01:55,290 --> 00:01:59,013
Venerable Sir, our knowledge of these things has its roots in the Blessed One.

12
00:01:59,375 --> 00:02:01,736
It has the Blessed One as guide and resort,

13
00:02:02,424 --> 00:02:06,850
It would be good, Venerable Sir, if the Blessed One would clarify the meaning of that statement.

14
00:02:07,350 --> 00:02:10,496
Having heard it from him, we will bear it in mind.

15
00:02:10,975 --> 00:02:11,776
That means us, you see.

16
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:17,745
Listen then, and attend carefully, I shall speak.

17
00:02:18,064 --> 00:02:22,151
Yes, Venerable Sir, they replied, and the Blessed One spoke thus.

18
00:02:24,454 --> 00:02:30,762
When an uninstructed worldly monk comes upon gain, they do not reflect on it thus.

19
00:02:31,112 --> 00:02:37,319
This gain that has come to me is impermanent, bound up with suffering and subject to change.

20
00:02:38,461 --> 00:02:40,283
They do not know it as it really is.

21
00:02:41,545 --> 00:02:47,573
And when they come upon loss, fame and disrepute, praise and blame, they do not reflect on them thus.

22
00:02:48,013 --> 00:02:51,997
All these are impermanent, bound up with suffering and subject to change.

23
00:02:53,259 --> 00:02:54,981
They do not see them as they really are.

24
00:02:56,503 --> 00:03:00,207
With such a person, gain and loss, fame and disrepute,

25
00:03:00,425 --> 00:03:05,372
praise and blame, pleasure and pain, keep their minds engrossed.

26
00:03:05,391 --> 00:03:08,276
And when gain comes, they are elated.

27
00:03:08,316 --> 00:03:12,122
And when they meet with loss, they are dejected.

28
00:03:13,925 --> 00:03:15,727
When fame comes, they are elated.

29
00:03:15,826 --> 00:03:18,752
And when they meet with disrepute, they are dejected.

30
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:21,556
When praise comes, they are elated.

31
00:03:21,596 --> 00:03:25,520
And when they meet with blame, they are dejected.

32
00:03:27,243 --> 00:03:29,486
And when they experience pleasure, they are elated.

33
00:03:30,293 --> 00:03:33,236
But when they experience pain, they're dejected.

34
00:03:33,957 --> 00:03:44,091
Being thus involved in likes and dislikes, they will not be free from birth, aging and death, from sorrow, lamentation, pain, dejection and despair.

35
00:03:44,671 --> 00:03:46,735
They will not be free from suffering, I say.

36
00:03:48,657 --> 00:03:54,865
But when an instructed noble disciple comes upon gain, they reflect it thus.

37
00:03:55,545 --> 00:03:56,967
This gain has come to me.

38
00:03:57,508 --> 00:04:00,132
This gain that has come to me is impermanent.

39
00:04:00,483 --> 00:04:03,006
bound up with suffering and subject to change.

40
00:04:03,725 --> 00:04:07,870
And so they will reflect when loss or so forth comes upon them.

41
00:04:08,691 --> 00:04:13,776
They understand all things as they really are and they do not engross their minds.

42
00:04:15,277 --> 00:04:30,473
Thus, they will not be elated by gain and dejected by loss, elated by fame and dejected by disrepute, elated by praise and dejected by blame, elated by pleasure

43
00:04:30,723 --> 00:04:43,596
and dejected by pain, and having thus given up likes and dislikes, they will be freed from birth, aging, and death, from sorrow, lamentation, pain, dejection, and despair.

44
00:04:43,636 --> 00:04:46,358
They will be free from suffering, I say.

45
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:56,629
This is the distinction, the disparity, the difference between an instructed noble disciple and an uninstructed worldling.

46
00:04:59,055 --> 00:04:59,355
clear?

47
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:05,142
so what's the Buddha saying here?

48
00:05:05,403 --> 00:05:28,471
these things I mean are pretty obvious some of them are pretty obvious to now you see so there are these eight worldly conditions gain and loss well I mean you know we've just been through this growth in the economy for eight years and then suddenly it collapses and while it grows nobody thinks this is going to end you know it's like this is going to go on forever

